good on the promise of public education      Working with the UIC College of Education, PIP offers Master of Education programs in Instructional Leadership, which have two concentrations: Educational Studies Concentration and Policy Studies Concentration. Participants in the programs take classes with regular UIC students. Courses are taught by UIC Faculty.  Please click here to learn more about the MEd Programs in Instructional Leadership at UIC.      Explore More:  College of Education          Programs    Back to main content           Public Administration Programs    Engineering Program    Education Program    Statistics Program    Economics Program    Urban Planning and Policy    Short-Term Training                  UIC Logo        Programs for International Partnerships         Quick Links    Handbook    Life In Chicago    About UIC         Contact   Programs for International Partnerships  1253 S. Halsted Street, Suite 204, Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: +1 (312) 996-0563  Fax: +1 (312) 996-6264  pip@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 